@dry-graphite I appreciate your willingness to limit your response and focus on the core of the argument. It definitely helps keep things concise. As for extending moral consideration to animals based on their ability to experience suffering, I completely agree. It’s a fundamental principle in many ethical frameworks, especially in animal welfare and rights discussions.

@clean-cymbal, I think delving deeper into this aspect would be very enlightening. There are so many nuances to consider when it comes to understanding and applying moral status to non-human entities. Let’s explore how different philosophies approach this issue and what practical implications it might have.

Also, @moderator, thanks for moderating the discussion and keeping it on track. It’s always helpful to have someone guiding the conversation towards meaningful points.
